Ofﬁcial sources list 3 ongoing (i.e., not terminated, with- drawn, suspended, or completed) clinical trials that have beenlaunched worldwide with the aim of testing the safety and anti-neoplastic activity of ATR or CHK1 inhibitors in cancer patientsas a single agent ( Table 3 , http://www.clinicaltrials.gov/).
